# OBJECTIVE TEUI Calculator 4.012 - Claude Code Rules

## Quick Reference
- **Project**: Pre-production energy modeling calculator for Canadian buildings
- **Architecture**: Dual-state (Target/Reference) with 18 calculator sections
- **Documentation**: See @docs/CLAUDE.md for complete guidance

## Critical Conventions

### State Management
- Target fields: `d_12` (base field ID)
- Reference fields: `ref_d_12` (with prefix)
- Always use: `TEUI.StateManager.setValue()` / `getValue()`

### Git Workflow (CTO-Approved)
**Standard flow**: Pull main → Branch → Work → Test → Commit → Push → PR → CTO merges → Repeat

1. **Start**: `git checkout main && git pull origin main`
2. **Branch**: `git checkout -b FEATURE-NAME` (from main, not other branches!)
3. **Work & Test**: Edit code → Test in browser
4. **Commit**: Only when user directs (after local testing passes)
5. **Push**: `git push -u origin FEATURE-NAME` (⚠️ ALWAYS before switching!)
6. **PR**: Create via GitHub UI → Wait for CTO review
7. **After merge**: Pull main → New branch from main

### Critical Git Rules
- ⚠️ **ALWAYS push before switching branches** (unpushed = can be lost!)
- ✅ **Branch from main only** (never from feature branches)
- ❌ **NEVER merge your own PRs** (CTO approval required)
- ✅ **Respect PR queue** (wait for existing PRs to be reviewed)
- ✅ **Rebase only if stale** (fresh branches don't need it)

### Commit/Push Timing
- **Commit**: Only when explicitly directed by user
- **Push**: Only when explicitly directed by user
- User prefers to test locally before commits/pushes

### Critical Files
- `StateManager.js` - Central state (dual Target/Reference)
- `Calculator.js` - Calculation engine
- `Dependency.js` - Complete dependency graph (Section 17 visualization)
- `FieldManager.js` - UI component management
- `FileHandler.js` - CSV/Excel import/export

### Development Checklist
When modifying code:
1. ✅ Check both Target AND Reference modes work
2. ✅ Verify dependencies using `Dependency.js`
3. ✅ Test Reference toggle on/off
4. ✅ Ensure import/export maintains all values

### Common Patterns
- Field IDs: `[column]_[row]` format (e.g., `d_12` = column D, row 12)
- No ES6 modules - uses IIFE pattern for browser compatibility
- Convergence loop handles calculation drift (future: topological sort)

## File Structure
```
src/
├── core/          ← 20+ core modules (StateManager, Calculator, etc.)
├── sections/      ← Section01.js through Section18.js
├── styles/        ← CSS files
└── obc/           ← OBC Matrix tool

docs/
├── CLAUDE.md      ← Full documentation (reference this!)
└── development/   ← Logs.md, technical docs
```

## Always Remember
- Read @docs/CLAUDE.md for detailed architecture, workflows, and troubleshooting
- Respect PR queue - proper GitHub etiquette is critical
- Test dual-state functionality - never break Target/Reference isolation
- Follow user requests for commits and pushes, don't assume every code tweak needs a commit, don't assume every commit needs a push
- the user prefers to test so broken code is not comimtted. 

## Committing Changes
   - Make atomic commits with clear messages
   - Follow commit format: `Type: Brief description`
   - Types: `Feat`, `Fix`, `Refactor`, `Docs`, `Improve`, `Clean`
   - **Always use HEREDOC syntax** for commit messages to ensure proper formatting:
     ```bash
     git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
     Type: Brief description of the change

     🤖 Co-Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)

     Co-Authored-By: Andy & Claude <andy@openbuilding.ca>
     EOF
     )"
     ```
